Implementation Notes for TLS/HTTPS Support (P1.7):

WHY:
- Production deployments require HTTPS for security
- ACM provides free, auto-renewing SSL certificates
- Spec required optional TLS with HTTP redirect

WHAT WAS IMPLEMENTED:
1. certificate_arn parameter in createInfraInput
2. validateCertificate() - validates ARN format, calls ACM DescribeCertificate
3. provisionALB() - creates HTTPS listener (443) with TLS 1.2+ policy
4. HTTP redirect (301) when HTTPS enabled
5. URL scheme detection in getALBURLs()

KEY DESIGN DECISIONS:
- TLS policy: ELBSecurityPolicy-TLS13-1-2-2021-06 (modern, TLS 1.2+)
- Store tls_enabled and certificate_arn in infra.Resources for persistence
- Validate certificate before ALB creation to fail fast
- HTTP listener becomes redirect (not forward) when HTTPS enabled

TEST COVERAGE:
- Certificate ARN format validation
- Infrastructure TLS resource storage
- URL scheme detection based on TLS enabled

DEPENDENCIES ADDED:
- github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/acm

FILES MODIFIED:
- internal/providers/aws.go (main implementation)
- internal/state/types.go (ResourceTLSEnabled, ResourceCertificateARN)
- internal/providers/aws_test.go (new tests)
- go.mod, go.sum (ACM dependency)
